name: Texas
notes: Texas does not use the letter 'O' on standard plates. Only the number zero '0' is used to avoid confusion. Common practice to omit confusing letters in general issue serials per TxDMV specs/manuals. Source: OOS.txt compilation - confirmed via Texas Department of Motor Vehicles documentation. Does not use letter 'O' on standard plates. Always use zero '0'.

stacked_characters.position: INCLUDE 'DV' stacked characters. OMIT letter 'T' in white part of plate.
stacked_characters.notes: Include DV stacked. Omit letter T in white part of plate.
